SUMMARY:Dragon Boat Eye Dotting Ceremony
DESCRIPTION:The Portland-Kaohsiung Sister City Association (PKSCA) is proud to present the Eye Dotting Ceremony\, signaling the start of the 12 week long Portland Rose Festival Dragon Boat Race season. A Buddhist Master from Portland Miao Fa Temple will conduct a formal Buddhist ceremony blessing the dragon boats. \nThe event includes the formal dotting of the eyes of the Traditional-style dragon boats by dignitaries\, and a parade of dragon boats with a Portland Fire Boat display. The ceremony is free and open to the public. The event begins outside the King Tide Fish & Shell restaurant at the Kimpton RiverPlace Hotel\, 1510 S Harbor Way\, Portland\, OR 97201 and finishes on the Riverplace Marina docks. \nThe event will be opened with a Chinese drum line performance! Local dragon boat teams will participate in a parade on the Willamette River\, while the Portland Fire Boat puts on a display.
URL:https://pdxparent.com/event-single/dragon-boat-eye-dotting-ceremony/
LOCATION:1510 S. Harbor Way\, 1510 S Harbor Way\, Portland\, Oregon
CATEGORIES:Kids Calendar,Music,Outdoor,Parade
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://pdxparent.com/wp-content/uploads/dragon-boat-eye-dotting-ceremony.jpg
END:VEVENT
